{"type":"message","id":"6cd31f7c","parentId":"a48a989c","timestamp":"2026-05-28T20:47:35.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the morningcourt cron job:\n\n1. The cron job is set for 08:00 daily, targeting session `agent:father:qqbot:direct:6687d4d2d1f8eda5231c6809b1a26204` (which is my main session with the user).\n2. The payload is an agentTurn with a message asking me to \"check morningcourt config and generate morning court briefing and push to user.\"\n3. It uses delivery mode \"announce\" to send to the user's QQ.\n\nNow, the problem: When this cron fires, it comes into **my session** as an agentTurn. I need to figure out:\n- What happens when this fires? It comes to me (Father) as a message.\n- I need to handle it - I should read the morningcourt config, then spawn Son with the right instruction.\n\nBut wait - this cron job was set up BEFORE our restructuring. The payload says \"请查阅 morningcourt 配置\" - it's asking me to figure it out. \n\nThe cron fires and sends a message to my session. I would need to:\n1. Read the config to understand what's needed\n2. Spawn Son with the morningcourt function\n\nLet me also check if the cron payload needs updating given our new routing (Father → Son direct).\n\nActually, looking at the cron payload more carefully:\n```\n\"早朝时间到！用户 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204（汀桑）的早朝播报。请查阅 morningcourt 配置，生成早朝简报并推送给用户。\"\n```\n\nWhen this fires, it sends an agentTurn to my session. I would process it - I'd see this message, recognize it's the morning court trigger, read the config, and spawn Son with `{function:morningcourt, action:manual, params:{sender_id:...}}`.\n\nThis should work as long as:\n1. The cron fires at 08:00 (next run: 1780012800000, which would be tomorrow at 08:00)\n2. I'm available to process it\n3. Son has the morningcourt_function.md in its functions/\n\nBut there's a potential issue: the cron says sessionTarget is `session:agent:father:qqbot:direct:6687d4d2d1f8eda5231c6809b1a26204` - this is my session with the user. The cron fires and injects a message into this ongoing session. That should be fine.\n\nActually, wait - there might be a routing issue. The cron payload's message is just a plain text description. When I receive it, I need to route it properly. My trigger_prompt.md handles `/早朝` etc. but the cron message won't match any trigger - it's just plain text saying \"早朝时间到...\"\n\nSo I need to make sure I know how to handle this message when it comes in. It's a system event, not a user message. Let me think...\n\nIn my session, when this agentTurn fires, it's like someone sent me a message. I would read it, understand it's the morning court trigger, and then spawn Son.\n\nActually, looking at it more carefully - this should still work fine. The cron fires, sends the message to my session, I read it, understand it's the morning court, and I spawn Son to generate the briefing. The only issue would be if I'm in the middle of another conversation, but that's a scheduling concern, not a routing concern.\n\nLet me just tell the user it's still working as expected.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"早朝官目前在跑，配置没问题：\n\n```\n⏰ 时间: 每天 08:00 (CST)\n📤 推送: → 你的 QQ 私聊\n✅ 状态: 启用\n```\n\n这个 cron 设的是 **sessionTarget 绑定到咱俩的对话 session**，到点就往我这儿丢一条消息让我处理。我收到后会 spawn Son 去组装早朝简报再推给你。\n\n**不过有一个点**——旧 cron payload 里写的是\"请查阅 morningcourt 配置\"，没写成结构化的指令。等我明天早上实际跑一次看看能不能正常出活。如果不行我改下 payload 让它更明确，比如直接写：\n\n```\n早朝时间到。读 morningcourt/config，spawn Son 执行 {function:morningcourt, action:manual}\n```\n\n明天 08:00 最先见分晓。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1337,"output":947,"cacheRead":57600,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":762,"totalTokens":59884,"cost":{"input":0.00018718,"output":0.00026516,"cacheRead":0.0016128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00206514}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780001240792,"responseId":"f4525d27-8336-41f6-974d-0eb89fbbb146"}}
