{"type":"message","id":"8fe1ef9a","parentId":"c5298df9","timestamp":"2026-05-28T20:48:31.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying I should make the morning court cron more explicit, and also need to handle the case where different users set different morning court times.\n\nLet me think about this. The current morningcourt feature works like this:\n1. User A sets `/设早朝 08:00` → creates a config file `config-{sender_id}.json` + creates a cron job\n2. The cron fires at 08:00 → sends a message to my session asking to generate briefing\n\nBut there's a design issue here:\n- Currently the cron job is tied specifically to the user's session: `session:agent:father:qqbot:direct:6687d4d2d1f8eda5231c6809b1a26204`\n- If we have multiple users, each would need their own cron job with their own session\n- The cron payload needs to be explicit about WHICH user is being served\n\nLet me check what the morningcourt_function.md says about how the cron is supposed to work, and then think about how to refactor it.\n\nLooking at the current cron job:\n- sessionTarget: `session:agent:father:qqbot:direct:6687d4d2d1f8eda5231c6809b1a26204` - tied to this user's session\n- payload: generic text asking to look up config\n\nThe problem: if there are multiple users, each needs their own cron. And the cron payload should be explicit about which user to serve, so I can just spawn Son directly with the right params.\n\nThe better design would be:\n1. Each morningcourt cron is per-user\n2. The cron payload explicitly says which user: `sender_id` and `time`\n3. When it fires, I just spawn Son: `{function:morningcourt, action:manual, params:{sender_id:\"...\"}}`\n4. Son reads the config, generates and announces the briefing\n\nActually, let me re-read the morningcourt_function.md to see what the intended design is.\n\nFrom what I read earlier, the `/设早朝` action:\n- Sets config-{sender_id}.json time\n- Notifies Father to create/update cron\n\nAnd `/关早朝`:\n- Sets config-{sender_id}.json enabled=false\n- Notifies Father to remove cron\n\nSo the flow for different users:\n1. 汀桑 sets 08:00 → creates cron for 汀桑\n2. 雾籽米 sets 07:00 → creates cron for 雾籽米\n\nEach cron should have the user's sender_id in the payload so I know who to serve.\n\nLet me update the cron payload to be explicit, and also update the morningcourt function definition to be clear about how the cron should be structured.\n\nActually, I should update:\n1. The existing cron job payload to be more explicit\n2. The morningcourt_function.md to specify the cron payload format\n3. My AGENTS.md to handle morningcourt cron properly\n\nLet me do this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"你说得对。不同用户设不同时间，每个 cron 必须带 clear 的 sender_id，这样我收到后直接 spawn Son，不用猜是谁。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_xS9W6J1wxezB48Rutd0b0529","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"557cdce4-3315-41d0-a7c9-37f069050678","patch":{"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"[morningcourt] sender_id=6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204, trigger briefing generation","timeoutSeconds":120}}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"update\", \"jobId\": \"557cdce4-3315-41d0-a7c9-37f069050678\", \"patch\": {\"payload\":{\"kind\":\"agentTurn\",\"message\":\"[morningcourt] sender_id=6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204, trigger briefing generation\",\"timeoutSeconds\":120}}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3579,"output":804,"cacheRead":56320,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":627,"totalTokens":60703,"cost":{"input":0.00050106,"output":0.00022512,"cacheRead":0.0015769599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00230314}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780001301338,"responseId":"bb953d1a-7938-4f2e-b080-4fe635491e6a"}}
