{"type":"message","id":"0e7731bd","parentId":"40636ff4","timestamp":"2026-05-28T21:11:10.858Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the current file, it seems like the agents list already has father, spirit, and son restored! The file already shows:\n\n1. father - with workspace /root/.openclaw/workspace-father\n2. spirit - with workspace /root/.openclaw/workspace-spirit  \n3. son - with workspace /root/.openclaw/workspace-son\n\nAnd son now has:\n- primary model: deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash\n- models include both DeepSeek and QwenVL\n\nSo the config is actually already correct! The file was written properly after my `--replace-path` attempt... wait, maybe the gateway config was read from a different source, or the config command I ran earlier actually patched the file properly somehow.\n\nActually no, looking more carefully at the file, the agents.list already has father and spirit back. This might mean the config was saved correctly after I patched it earlier and the file structure was maintained.\n\nWait, let me re-check - earlier when I ran `openclaw config get agents`, it only showed son in the list. But now when I read the actual openclaw.json file, it shows all three agents (father, spirit, son) with the correct config.\n\nHmm, maybe the earlier `openclaw config get agents` output was before the file was rewritten, or maybe the file was fixed by the gateway startup process. Either way, the current config looks correct now.\n\nLet me verify:\n- The agents.list has father, spirit, and son with proper workspaces ✓\n- son's primary model is deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash ✓\n- son has QwenVL secondary model for image tasks ✓\n- All three qqbot bindings point to father ✓\n- Everything else looks the same as before ✓\n\nSo actually, the issue I thought happened may have been corrected by the runtime, or the config I read earlier was incomplete. Either way, the file now looks correct.\n\nBut wait - I should check if the gateway needs restarting. The config was already patched and the gateway was restarted (it got SIGTERM). Let me check if things are running now.\n\nAlso, I need to note that when spawning Son for image tasks (相册存照片), I should use the QwenVL model. Let me also update my AGENTS.md to make this clear.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"还好，实际读文件是好的——father、spirit、son 三个都在，只有 son 的 model 改成了 DeepSeek，保留了 QwenVL 备选。没搞丢。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BHXMbx0KKY8ROXf3ugRM7311","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get agents 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor agent in d.get('list', []):\n    m = agent.get('model',{}).get('primary','?')\n    ws = agent.get('workspace','-')\n    print(f\\\"{agent['id']}: model={m}, workspace={ws}\\\")\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"openclaw config get agents 2>&1 | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nfor agent in d.get('list', []):\\n    m = agent.get('model',{}).get('primary','?')\\n    ws = agent.get('workspace','-')\\n    print(f\\\\\\\"{agent['id']}: model={m}, workspace={ws}\\\\\\\")\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3021,"output":662,"cacheRead":69504,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":494,"totalTokens":73187,"cost":{"input":0.00042294,"output":0.00018536,"cacheRead":0.0019461119999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002554412}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780002663021,"responseId":"57584f31-0aa5-4dd4-91f9-bcf106a29515"}}
