{"type":"message","id":"ac5d537f","parentId":"cb7acd62","timestamp":"2026-05-28T21:15:19.130Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if there's a way to \"weld\" (firmly bind) the Father agent to qqbot - essentially making sure that Father is the only agent that handles qqbot messages, and that it's locked in place so it can't be changed accidentally.\n\nLooking at the current config, the binding is done through `bindings`:\n\n```json\n\"bindings\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"route\",\n      \"agentId\": \"father\",\n      \"match\": {\n        \"channel\": \"qqbot\",\n        \"accountId\": \"bot1\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"route\",\n      \"agentId\": \"father\",\n      \"match\": {\n        \"channel\": \"qqbot\",\n        \"accountId\": \"bot2\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"route\",\n      \"agentId\": \"father\",\n      \"match\": {\n        \"channel\": \"qqbot\",\n        \"accountId\": \"bot3\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n```\n\nThis already routes all qqbot traffic to Father. But I think the user wants it to be more locked down - maybe they want to configure it so that only Father can handle qqbot, and perhaps prevent other agents from accidentally being bound to qqbot.\n\nActually, I think what the user is really getting at is:\n- The config is currently set up with bindings routing qqbot → Father\n- But there's nothing preventing someone (like me being careless earlier) from accidentally changing the config\n- They want some kind of safeguard\n\nOne approach would be to also set restrictions on the other agents so they don't accept qqbot channels. I'm not sure if OpenClaw has a \"deny channel\" config option for agents.\n\nLet me look at what config options are available for agents to restrict channel access.\n\nActually, looking at the current config more carefully, the bindings already do exactly what the user wants. The bindings section is pretty clear. But the user might be concerned about someone accidentally changing them.\n\nLet me think about practical solutions:\n1. The bindings are already in place - that's the correct way\n2. We could add comments/documentation in the config file\n3. We could set up permissions/restrictions on the son/spirit agents\n4. We could back up the config\n\nActually, I think the user might be concerned about the `--replace-path` mistake I made earlier where I accidentally replaced the entire agent list. They want to make sure the Father↔qqbot binding can't be accidentally overwritten.\n\nThe reality is: the bindings section in openclaw.json is the correct place, and they're already set. The issue wasn't that the bindings were wrong, it was that I accidentally replaced the agents list. The bindings section was untouched.\n\nBut maybe there's a more direct way to express this. Let me look at agent-level config options.\n\nActually, looking at the channel config, there's `allowFrom` and `groupAllowFrom` which restrict who can message. There might be similar restrictions at the agent level.\n\nLet me check what config options are available.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UXAlneg5KAUrDQUrOPHD5499","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config schema lookup 2>&1 | head -5; echo \"---\"; openclaw config schema lookup --path channels 2>&1 || echo \"no channels schema\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"openclaw config schema lookup 2>&1 | head -5; echo \\\"---\\\"; openclaw config schema lookup --path channels 2>&1 || echo \\\"no channels schema\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1967,"output":735,"cacheRead":74112,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":654,"totalTokens":76814,"cost":{"input":0.00027538000000000004,"output":0.00020580000000000002,"cacheRead":0.002075136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002556316}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780002909385,"responseId":"0cba58e7-98d5-4132-bc7c-8e74c