{"type":"message","id":"b708c55d","parentId":"4a433731","timestamp":"2026-05-28T21:15:41.406Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ET_P9vKLduYDNPie24Sh6qL9883","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"      agents: {\n        list: [\n          { id: \"home\", default: true, workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-home\" },\n          { id: \"work\", workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-work\" },\n        ],\n      },\n      bindings: [\n        { agentId: \"home\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"personal\" } },\n        { agentId: \"work\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"biz\" } },\n      ],\n    }\n    ```\n\n    See [Multi-Agent](/concepts/multi-agent) and [full reference](/gateway/config-agents#multi-agent-routing) for binding rules and per-agent access profiles.\n\n  </Accordion>\n\n  <Accordion title=\"Split config into multiple files ($include)\">\n    Use `$include` to organize large configs:\n\n    ```json5\n    // ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n    {\n      gateway: { port: 18789 },\n      agents: { $include: \"./agents.json5\" },\n      broadcast: {\n        $include: [\"./clients/a.json5\", \"./clients/b.json5\"],\n      },\n    }\n    ```\n\n[230 more lines in file. Use offset=510 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780002941405}}
{"type":"message","id":"307962a2","parentId":"b708c55d","timestamp":"2026-05-28T21:15:45.272Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the current bindings setup is the standard way to route channel traffic to a specific agent. The user is asking if there's a way to \"weld\" Father to qqbot. \n\nThe current setup already does this through bindings. But given my earlier mistake with `--replace-path`, the user might be concerned about accidental changes.\n\nLet me think of practical solutions:\n\n1. **The bindings are already correct** - they route all three qqbot accounts to Father\n2. **We could add explicit comments in the config** - OpenClaw uses JSON5 so comments are supported\n3. **We could add a constraint/restriction to Son and Spirit** - so they can't receive qqbot messages even accidentally\n4. **Config backup** - automate backups\n\nActually, I think there might be a concept of \"deny channels\" per agent or something similar. Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OGvIPoJeZd1LARPZrX9I0505","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"channel.*deny\\|deny.*channel\\|restrict.*channel\\|channel.*allow\\|allowFrom\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md 2>/dev/null | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -r \\\"channel.*deny\\\\|deny.*channel\\\\|restrict.*channel\\\\|channel.*allow\\\\|allowFrom\\\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md 2>/dev/null | head -20\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":417,"output":282,"cacheRead":79232,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":187,"totalTokens":79931,"cost":{"input":0.00005838000000000001,"output":0.00007896,"cacheRead":0.002218496,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002355836}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780002941423,"responseId":"f7b83146-0870-48b0-8f6b-00d300f65490"}}
