{"type":"message","id":"25a41240","parentId":"f59c8a1a","timestamp":"2026-05-28T21:15:47.767Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_WE44mEnydcc4GBc0GcdV6718","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"41:## Agent defaults, multi-agent, sessions, and messages\n47:- `multiAgent.*` (multi-agent routing and bindings)\n247:conversation bindings, or any non-Codex harness.\n410:- `existing-session` profiles keep the current Chrome MCP route limits:\n547:  it if an externally configured Funnel route already covers the gateway port.\n712:- `agentId` routes to a specific agent; unknown IDs fall back to the default agent.\n742:      model: \"openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free\",\n778:- Non-loopback binds: canvas routes require Gateway auth (token/password/trusted-proxy), same as other Gateway HTTP surfaces."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":117,"aggregated":"41:## Agent defaults, multi-agent, sessions, and messages\n47:- `multiAgent.*` (multi-agent routing and bindings)\n247:conversation bindings, or any non-Codex harness.\n410:- `existing-session` profiles keep the current Chrome MCP route limits:\n547:  it if an externally configured Funnel route already covers the gateway port.\n712:- `agentId` routes to a specific agent; unknown IDs fall back to the default agent.\n742:      model: \"openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free\",\n778:- Non-loopback binds: canvas routes require Gateway auth (token/password/trusted-proxy), same as other Gateway HTTP surfaces.","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780002947766}}
{"type":"message","id":"390604f9","parentId":"25a41240","timestamp":"2026-05-28T21:15:53.686Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I think the bindings section in the existing config is the correct way to do this. There isn't a specific \"deny channel\" config for agents.\n\nThe practical ways to \"weld\" Father to qqbot would be:\n\n1. **The bindings already do this** - all qqbot traffic → Father\n2. **Don't add route bindings for Son or Spirit** to qqbot (which we haven't done)\n3. **Back up the config** to recover from mistakes\n4. **Add comments in openclaw.json** to make the binding clear and prevent accidental changes\n\nLet me suggest concrete practical steps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"现在 bindings 已经是焊死的：\n\n```json\n\"bindings\": [\n  { \"agentId\": \"father\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"qqbot\", \"accountId\": \"bot1\" } },\n  { \"agentId\": \"father\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"qqbot\", \"accountId\": \"bot2\" } },\n  { \"agentId\": \"father\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"qqbot\", \"accountId\": \"bot3\" } }\n]\n```\n\n只要不删这段，所有 QQ 消息永远是 Father 接。要彻底焊死可以加几道锁：\n\n**1. 备份 + 注释**\n配置是 JSON5，支持注释。直接写死在文件里：\n\n```json5\n// ⚠️ 警告：所有 qqbot 消息固定路由到 father\n// 不要修改 bindings 段，不要将 qqbot 路由到其他 agent\nbindings: [\n  { agentId: \"father\", match: { channel: \"qqbot\", accountId: \"bot1\" } },\n  ...\n]\n```\n\n**2. 配置自动备份**\n设个 crontab 每天备份一次 `openclaw.json`：\n\n```bash\n0 4 * * * cp ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json ~/.openclaw/backups/openclaw.json.$(date +\\%Y\\%m\\%d)\n```\n\n**3. 改配置前 spawn 子 agent 操作**\n你交代改配置的时候，我 spawn 一个子 agent 去干，搞砸了直接关掉不影响主 session。\n\n---\n\n要我加注释和设自动备份吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":205,"output":483,"cacheRead":80000,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":133,"totalTokens":80688,"cost":{"input":0.000028700000000000003,"output":0.00013524,"cacheRead":0.00224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00240394}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780002947778,"responseId":"9ffd6b78-5f6c-4072-8bfc-a141bddb5f7e"}}
