{"type":"message","id":"b1bf883f","parentId":"ad26d188","timestamp":"2026-05-29T05:26:34.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says they didn't receive the morning court briefing at 08:00. So the delivery status \"not-delivered\" was correct - the morning court briefing generated at 08:00 never actually reached the user's QQ.\n\nThis means I need to check why the delivery failed. Looking at the cron configuration:\n\n```json\n\"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"to\": \"qqbot:c2c:6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204\",\n    \"channel\": \"qqbot\",\n    \"accountId\": \"bot1\"\n}\n```\n\nAnd the cron fired at 08:00, I spawned Son, Son generated the briefing... but the delivery to QQ didn't work.\n\nThe issue might be that when I spawn Son in a subagent session, Son's output is announced back to the parent session (my session), but the cron's delivery mode is \"announce\" which should deliver to the user's QQ. But since I'm in the middle of processing the cron message, maybe the delivery chain got confused.\n\nActually, looking at the cron setup more carefully:\n- The cron sends an agentTurn to my session (the message I received at 08:00)\n- I spawn Son as a subagent\n- Son generates the briefing\n- Son returns to me\n- The cron delivery should then send my final reply to the user\n\nBut since I yielded and waited for Son, and then the briefing text came back... I think what happened is that the system announced Son's output (the briefing) to me (Father's session), but the delivery announcement chain didn't route it to the user's QQ properly.\n\nActually, looking at the message flow: I spawned Son, yielded, Son completed, and then I replied with the briefing text as my response. My response should have been delivered to the user automatically since this is a qqbot direct session.\n\nBut the user says they didn't receive it at 08:00. So something in the delivery chain failed.\n\nNow we have a second trigger at 13:25. Let me handle this one differently - instead of yielding and hoping delivery works, let me spawn Son now and deliver directly.\n\nWait, actually the user is chatting with me right now (13:26). So this IS the second trigger attempt. Let me generate the briefing now and send it directly.\n\nLet me spawn Son to generate the briefing, and then deliver the result to the user.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"确实没送达，那早上那趟白跑了。现在再跑一次，这次直接送："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_w5DfbwzHaQBO58nGqys93205","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"son","mode":"run","task":"{\"function\":\"morningcourt\",\"action\":\"manual\",\"params\":{\"sender_id\":\"6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204\"}}"},"partialArgs":"{\"agentId\": \"son\", \"mode\": \"run\", \"task\": \"{\\\"function\\\":\\\"morningcourt\\\",\\\"action\\\":\\\"manual\\\",\\\"params\\\":{\\\"sender_id\\\":\\\"6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204\\\"}}\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":6230,"output":647,"cacheRead":85632,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":512,"totalTokens":92509,"cost":{"input":0.0008722000000000001,"output":0.00018116,"cacheRead":0.002397696,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003451056}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780032387539,"responseId":"f0856cd6-fd5e-445a-be19-47fce512b6db"}}
