{"type":"message","id":"4e739ed2","parentId":"fbb0ef81","timestamp":"2026-05-29T06:42:48.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says that 雾籽米 uses bot2 (accountId: bot2). Let me check the channels config - we have bot1, bot2, bot3 all configured under qqbot. \n\nSo 雾籽米 sends messages through bot2's qqbot channel. But the thing is, I can't proactively send a message to them unless I have an active session with them. Let me check if there's a sessions_send option available.\n\nActually, looking at my tools, I have `sessions_send` which can send a message to a visible session by sessionKey, agentId, etc. But I don't think I have a session with 雾籽米 since they never messaged me.\n\nWait - the user said 雾籽米 is \"第二个注册的人\". The user who registered 雾籽米 as a user... was it the user saying that 雾籽米 exists as a user? Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, looking at the users directory:\n- 346E6B5AF511B67156BF9130F0FCB06D - 雾籽米 - created from registration process\n- 468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B - new person who messaged at 13:46\n\n雾籽米 is a registered user entry but they haven't actually messaged the bot yet. The User.md entry exists but there's no session history. So I can't directly message them.\n\nHowever, the user says 雾籽米 uses bot2. So when 雾籽米 eventually sends a message to bot2, it'll route to me (Father) and I can then pass along the message.\n\nBut the user wants me to proactively ask 雾籽米 about 巧乐兹. Since there's no active session, I can't really push a message out.\n\nLet me be honest about this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"啊，bot2——那雾籽米是走第二个QQ机器人账号的。\n\n不过问题还是那个——雾籽米没给我发过消息，我没法主动给ta推送。得等ta先来找我，我才能把话递过去。\n\n要不这样：\n1. 你直接把雾籽米的QQ号给我，我记下来\n2. 等ta下次给bot2发消息的时候，我第一时间把你这个问题转过去\n\n或者你自己先跟ta说一声\"你找那个机器人聊聊\"，ta来问我了我就帮你带话。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":749,"output":509,"cacheRead":102272,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningT