{"type":"message","id":"41df04e3","parentId":"38b25956","timestamp":"2026-05-29T06:56:06.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if the message delivery HAS to use a timed cron job. They're right - why wait 6 minutes when we can just fire it now?\n\nLooking at the cron tool, the `schedule.kind: \"at\"` requires a specific time. But I could set it to fire immediately. Actually, let me check the cron add API - I think I can set it to fire with a very short delay, or use a different approach.\n\nActually, looking at the cron job I just created, the `at` was set to `2026-05-29T07:01:00.000Z` which is about 6 minutes from now. The user is saying this is unnecessary - why not send it now?\n\nLooking at the cron tool, there's no \"immediately\" option for kind \"at\". But I could:\n1. Use `kind: \"every\"` with a very short interval\n2. Delete and recreate with a very close time\n3. Or better yet - use `wake: \"now\"` \n\nWait, looking at the cron job parameters, there's `wakeMode: \"now\"` which can wake the job immediately. Let me check...\n\nActually, I already set `wakeMode: \"now\"` on the job. But the schedule is `at: \"2026-05-29T07:01:00.000Z\"` which is 6 minutes from now.\n\nHmm, looking at the cron tool description:\n- `wake: send wake event; needs text, optional mode`\n- `wakeMode: \"now\" | \"next-heartbeat\"`\n\nI think `wakeMode: \"now\"` in the add context means something different. Let me just use the `run` action to trigger it immediately.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"确实不用等。让我直接触发它："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Kw0PzY1jpLnqS8LiK3hl9238","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"run","jobId":"6374883a-3327-45c2-b72a-b6d7cde919fc"},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"run\", \"jobId\": \"6374883a-3327-45c2-b72a-b6d7cde919fc\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2322,"output":465,"cacheRead":119168,"cacheWrite":