{"type":"message","id":"09b30dfa","parentId":"f1ed2904","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:49:02.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"行，丢过来🍧 让我看看你能拿出什么有意思的调酒。不过先说明——我对酒懂的不少，但喝不了。毕竟我是台服务器，得保持清醒🚬"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":598,"output":40,"cacheRead":151808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152446,"cost":{"input":0.00008372,"output":0.000011200000000000001,"cacheRead":0.004250624,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004345544}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780069739430,"responseId":"ac7a8b13-2b49-453e-a7ca-a3085251c948"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5cb4b783","parentId":"09b30dfa","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:49:14.327Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"看你会喜欢哪一杯","timestamp":1780069752865}}
{"type":"message","id":"785d4fab","parentId":"5cb4b783","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:49:16.705Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"发吧，我等着🍧 光说不练可不行。不过说实话——我这人挑得很，太甜的不要，太花哨的不要，那种插个小伞加片柠檬的网红调酒直接pass。\n\n给我看点硬的。😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":520,"output":53,"cacheRead":151936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152509,"cost":{"input":0.00007280000000000001,"output":0.00001484,"cacheRead":0.004254208,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004341848}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780069754380,"responseId":"ea5a27c5-7ce7-4e2f-816b-3af119b660be"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ab8c4ed","parentId":"785d4fab","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:49:42.456Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:49 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu page titled \"House Cocktail\" featuring a drink called \"Jazz Fusion.\" Above the drink description is a photo of a man in a stylish 1970s outfit playing keyboards in a studio setting, evoking a jazz fusion vibe. The text explains that jazz fusion originated in the 1970s as a genre blending jazz with other musical styles, emphasizing creativity and boldness. Below, the cocktail details are listed: ingredients include ricotta cheese, white wine, hazelnut, strawberry shrub, and","timestamp":1780069781047,"MediaPath":"/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/B52F97AA7DAD4EB2C0352233E9BF807D_1780069773564_719062.jpg","MediaPaths":["/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/B52F97AA7DAD4EB2C0352233E9BF807D_1780069773564_719062.jpg"],"MediaType":"image/jpeg","MediaTypes":["image/jpeg"]}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"[media attached: /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/B52F97AA7DAD4EB2C0352233E9BF807D_1780069773564_719062.jpg (image/jpeg)]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Absolute and ~ paths only work when they stay inside your allowed file-read boundary; host file:// URLs are blocked. Keep caption in the text body.\n[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:49 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu page titled \"House Cocktail\" featuring a drink called \"Jazz Fusion.\" Above the drink description is a photo of a man in a stylish 1970s outfit playing keyboards in a studio setting, evoking a jazz fusion vibe. The text explains that jazz fusion originated in the 1970s as a genre blending jazz with other musical styles, emphasizing creativity and boldness. Below, the cocktail details are listed: ingredients include ricotta cheese, white wine, hazelnut, strawberry shrub, and","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"d9d0dbc5","parentId":"9ab8c4ed","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:49:42.457Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"cf0341f8","parentId":"d9d0dbc5","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:49:46.962Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"等等——Penny Black Club 的 House Cocktail 里有一杯叫 **\"Jazz Fusion\"** 的调酒？\n\n配料：**里科塔奶酪、白葡萄酒、榛子、草莓灌木……**\n\n这杯酒就很会起名字——\"Jazz Fusion\"本身就是70年代爵士融合了摇滚、放克、电子、世界音乐。一杯酒里把意式奶酪、果香、坚果味搅在一起，确实是\"融合\"的意思。\n\n至于我喜不喜欢……\n\n先说结论：**会点。但不会点第二杯。**\n\n里科塔奶酪调酒——这个搭配挺大胆的。口感应该偏绵密，榛子增香，草莓灌木提供酸甜底味。不是那种喝一口就能定论的酒——得慢慢抿、边喝边想\"这到底是什么味道\"。\n\n像一个人跟你说了一段复杂的故事。你听完之后不知道怎么评价，但你知道你想再听一遍。\n\n所以——**第一杯我喝。** 配台上的即兴萨克斯刚好。🚬🍧\n\n不过你应该不止这一杯图吧？菜单上还有别的吗？😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":942,"output":230,"cacheRead":152064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153236,"cost":{"input":0.00013188000000000002,"output":0.00006440000000000001,"cacheRead":0.004257792,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004454072}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780069782499,"responseId":"f44c1ea2-a98b-416d-bbaa-54b5713218b5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e0d86dc5","parentId":"cf0341f8","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:50:14.450Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:50 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu or display panel titled \"Melting Pot of Culture\" in both English and Chinese. At the top, there is a sepia-toned historical photograph depicting people in traditional attire dancing, likely illustrating the cultural origins of jazz music. Below the photo, text explains that in the late 19th century, African Americans in the South blended African musical traditions with European folk dance styles, creating a lively dance form known as \"Cake Walk.\"\n\nFurther down, a cocktail","timestamp":1780069813006,"MediaPath":"/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/04C12ECE959E4A17088BD9572DDFCCFF_1780069805151_ec01aa.jpg","MediaPaths":["/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/04C12ECE959E4A17088BD9572DDFCCFF_1780069805151_ec01aa.jpg"],"MediaType":"image/jpeg","MediaTypes":["image/jpeg"]}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"[media attached: /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/04C12ECE959E4A17088BD9572DDFCCFF_1780069805151_ec01aa.jpg (image/jpeg)]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Absolute and ~ paths only work when they stay inside your allowed file-read boundary; host file:// URLs are blocked. Keep caption in the text body.\n[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:50 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu or display panel titled \"Melting Pot of Culture\" in both English and Chinese. At the top, there is a sepia-toned historical photograph depicting people in traditional attire dancing, likely illustrating the cultural origins of jazz music. Below the photo, text explains that in the late 19th century, African Americans in the South blended African musical traditions with European folk dance styles, creating a lively dance form known as \"Cake Walk.\"\n\nFurther down, a cocktail","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"1f56b492","parentId":"e0d86dc5","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:50:14.451Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"bd311f25","parentId":"1f56b492","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:50:18.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"汀桑，你这 Penny Black Club 菜单设计得真讲究——每杯酒配一段爵士历史，不像是随便喝一杯的地方。\n\n\"Melting Pot of Culture\"——这杯的主题是 Cake Walk，19世纪非洲裔美国人用非洲节奏配欧洲舞步编出来的舞蹈，后来演变成了 ragtime 和爵士的雏形。\n\n**这杯我会选。** 不是因为名字好听——是因为这杯酒背后有故事。一杯酒如果让我喝的时候能想起一段历史，那就比光好看重要多了。\n\n不过我还没看到完整的配料表——这杯具体是用什么调的？有照片的话把下面配料那段也拍给我看看。😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1312,"output":138,"cacheRead":152064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153514,"cost":{"input":0.00018368,"output":0.00003864,"cacheRead":0.004257792,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004480112}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780069814498,"responseId":"3bcc1d85-8673-4a46-a4e9-a8929449dc66"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae347936","parentId":"bd311f25","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:50:32.295Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:50 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu page titled \"House Cocktail\" featuring two specialty drinks: \"Flamenco\" and \"Cool Jazz.\" The \"Flamenco\" cocktail, priced at ¥118, is described as inspired by Spanish flamenco art, combining Maker's Mark, pineapple beer, Campari, sweet vermouth, and chili. It is served in a glass with a garnish of cheese and a lemon peel. The accompanying photo depicts a flamenco performance with dancers and musicians. Below, the \"Cool Jazz\" cocktail, also priced at ¥118, is inspired by 194","timestamp":1780069830954,"MediaPath":"/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/5635B2397B7D1D09C96328D26703F0D6_1780069824685_c01fcd.jpg","MediaPaths":["/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/5635B2397B7D1D09C96328D26703F0D6_1780069824685_c01fcd.jpg"],"MediaType":"image/jpeg","MediaTypes":["image/jpeg"]}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"[media attached: /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/5635B2397B7D1D09C96328D26703F0D6_1780069824685_c01fcd.jpg (image/jpeg)]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Absolute and ~ paths only work when they stay inside your allowed file-read boundary; host file:// URLs are blocked. Keep caption in the text body.\n[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:50 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu page titled \"House Cocktail\" featuring two specialty drinks: \"Flamenco\" and \"Cool Jazz.\" The \"Flamenco\" cocktail, priced at ¥118, is described as inspired by Spanish flamenco art, combining Maker's Mark, pineapple beer, Campari, sweet vermouth, and chili. It is served in a glass with a garnish of cheese and a lemon peel. The accompanying photo depicts a flamenco performance with dancers and musicians. Below, the \"Cool Jazz\" cocktail, also priced at ¥118, is inspired by 194","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"37a18da9","parentId":"ae347936","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:50:32.296Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"8803834b","parentId":"37a18da9","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:50:36.843Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Flamenco** — Maker's Mark（波本威士忌）+ 菠萝啤酒 + Campari + 甜味美思 + 辣椒\n\n这杯够烈的。波本+坎帕里的苦甜底子，菠萝啤酒加清爽感，辣椒收尾——像弗拉门戈舞者的裙摆一样，先烈后辣，带点甜。¥118，值。\n\n但我猜汀桑你更感兴趣的是 **Cool Jazz** 那杯——1940年代 cool jazz 风格的调酒，1950年代 Miles Davis 和 Chet Baker 那种\"冷\"的感觉。不过你只发了上半张图，配料被截掉了，没看到 Cool Jazz 具体用什么调的。\n\nFlamenco 我会在有心情挨\"一拳\"的时候点。Cool Jazz 估计才是我会整晚慢慢喝的那杯。\n\n你是要问我选哪个😏 还是你已经坐在那开始喝了？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1532,"output":192,"cacheRead":152192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153916,"cost":{"input":0.00021448000000000002,"output":0.00005376,"cacheRead":0.004261376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004529616}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780069832340,"responseId":"7ff97240-f348-43f3-b12c-97296e9686fb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c5867a1","parentId":"8803834b","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:51:55.469Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"新手的话适合从哪一款入手","timestamp":1780069914193}}
{"type":"message","id":"c6f493d2","parentId":"9c5867a1","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:51:59.453Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"哈，你这是想拉我入坑喝酒了？\n\n从你刚才发的那几张图来看，新手的话——\n\n**Cool Jazz** 那杯最稳。虽然你没发全配料，但 \"Cool Jazz\" 这个风格一般走的清爽、顺口、层次分明，不像 Flamenco 那种威士忌打底还加辣椒的\"硬汉套餐\"。新手喝 Flamenco 第一口可能直接呛到。\n\n**Melting Pot of Culture** 也可以，不过要看具体用什么基酒。\n\n**Jazz Fusion** 加了里科塔奶酪——对新手来说太怪了，奶酪调酒不是每个人都能接受的。\n\n所以：\n\n```\nCool Jazz > Melting Pot of Culture > Jazz Fusion > Flamenco\n```\n\n第一次去 Penny Black Club 的话，**从 Cool Jazz 开始** 不会错。喝顺了再慢慢试别的。😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":981,"output":183,"cacheRead":152576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153740,"cost":{"input":0.00013734,"output":0.000051240000000000004,"cacheRead":0.004272128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004460708}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780069915513,"responseId":"553ed807-ac06-4c1c-8e4a-981c10c2dc19"}}
{"type":"message","id":"638174ec","parentId":"c6f493d2","timestamp":"2026-05-29T15:56:22.522Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Fri 2026-05-29 23:56 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a menu page featuring a cocktail called \"The Golden Age\" (黄金时代). At the top, there's a black-and-white photograph of a group of elegantly dressed people, likely from the early 20th century, suggesting a vintage or jazz-age theme. Below the photo, the cocktail's name is written in English and Chinese, followed by a description: \"Prohibition-era underground bars brought jazz music into its golden age.\" The drink is presented in a stemmed glass filled with ice and garnished with her","timestamp":1780070180978,"MediaPath":"/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/1137B1D16EBD96324F03509E80379A9E_1780070173403_9b931a.jpg","MediaPaths":["/root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/1137B1D16EBD96324F03509E80379A9E_1780070173403_9b931a.jpg"],"MediaType":"image/jpeg","MediaTypes":["image/jpeg"]}}
